-- Housing Development Plans to Raise 5 Billion Rupees Selling Five-Year Debt
-- Suprotip Ghosh
-- 2010-06-21T07:21:11Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-06-21/housing-development-plans-to-raise-5-billion-rupees-selling-five-year-debt.html

          
          
             Housing Development Finance Corp. ,
Indiaâ€™s third-largest lender by market value, is selling 5
billion rupees ($110 million) of five-year bonds, according to
two people familiar with the sale.  
 The issue pays a coupon of 8.3 percent, the people said.
Axis Bank Ltd., ICICI Bank Ltd. and ICICI Securities Primary
Dealership Ltd. were the arrangers of the deal, which will be
completed on June 23, the people said, declining to be
identified as the talks are private.  
